observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed to:
a) Identify the cost of road lot;
b) Reclassify erroneously recorded road pavement to the appropriate classification. Henceforth, ensure correct categorization of road components;
c) Provide complete description and cost segregation of road asset components in the subsidiary ledgers; and
d) Reconcile the PPELC for road network with the LRNLC. Moreover, update the LRNLC regularly to ensure consistent and accurate reporting.

We recommended that Management:
a) Instruct the engineering office to facilitate the programming of the identified proposed infrastructure projects funded out of the Municipal Development Fund;
b) Advise the BAC to fast track the bidding and procurement process of the 39 unimplemented projects costing ₱14.404 million;
c) Instruct the Municipal Development Council to carefully evaluate feasibility of the projects, especially those that have not been started. If not viable, revert the funds to the unappropriated DF for re-appropriation to other priority projects;
d) Instruct concerned Municipal Officials to closely monitor the implementation of the identified development projects especially those from previous years’ budget; and
e) Ensure that the development projects are completed within the timetable set.

We recommended that Management:
a) Comply with Section 22 of the CSC Omnibus Rules on leave that only employees with accumulated 15 days VL should be allowed to monetize a minimum of ten days with at least five days retained, and provided further that a maximum of 30 days is monetized within a given year;
b) Strictly observe the existing CSC and COA rules and regulations on the conditions for the monetization of 50 percent or more of the leave credits of officials and employees.

13.7. We recommended that Management:
13.7.1. Comply with Section 22 of the CSC Omnibus Rules on leave that only employees with accumulated 15 days VL should be allowed to monetize a minimum of ten days with at least five days retained, and provided further that a maximum of 30 days is monetized within a given year;
13.7.2. Strictly observe the existing CSC and COA rules and regulations on the conditions for the monetization of 50 percent or more of the leave credits of officials and employees;
13.7.3. Effect the necessary adjustment in the leave cards of employees whose monetization were deducted from their SL instead of VL; and
13.7.4. Submit immediately the approved leave application with certification of leave credit balance to support the payment of monetization of a Sanggunian Bayan member under Journal Entry Voucher No. 2019-02-123 for proper verification of the Audit Team.

17.6. We recommended that Management:
17.6.1. Revert the unutilized funds of the unimplemented ineligible projects for re-appropriation to other development projects identified under Item 3 of JMC No. 2017-1;
17.6.2. Henceforth, strictly follow the provisions of JMC No. 2017-1 dated February 22, 2017 in identifying PPAs to be funded out of the 20 percent DF to ensure that desirable socio-economic development is attained.

18.6. We recommended that Management:
18.6.1. Consider the quantity and nature of development projects being proposed for inclusion in the budget so that these are proportionate to the capacity of available resources, especially the manpower resources of the Municipal Engineering Office;
18.6.2. Review the technical viability of prior years’ unimplemented PPAs to determine whether there is a need to re-appropriate the amount to other priority PPAs of the Municipality;
18.6.3. Fast track the implementation of the unimplemented PPAs to bring development in the community for the welfare of the public;
18.6.4. Formulate/develop specific strategies/solutions to effectively implement development projects. Properly plan the timely procurement and implementation of all identified priority development projects to ensure prompt accomplishment of the same.

We recommended that the Treasury Office and the Accounting Department :

Reconcile the property records they maintain; 

Verify and analyse the discrepancies and promptly adjust the affected PPE accounts; 

Furnish the Audit Team with a copy of IIRUP to support the derecognition of PPE items from their respective books of accounts; and 

In case of PPE acquired from various donors, obtain necessary documents to support such donation.

